caption: This place is so good I am tempted to ask for a job if they pay me in baguettes and cinnamon rolls!  My wife and I love this bakery. Small little nugget in Bushwick. Their cold sandwiches are amazing. Their coffee is terrific and their nutella banana croissant is to die for! Everything is fresh, and they even make their Nutella!

We got a baguette (we cut up and freeze to eat throughout the week) and a slice of carrot cake. The carrot cake was delicious with generous frosting, the bread was perfectly crusty on the outside and soft/billowy inside. Customer service was very friendly and fast. Will definitely return, thank you!
Amazing bakery with awesome service. I highly recommend ordering from here, they have an awesome selection and the staff are super sweet too.
Great organic coffee & the Almond croissant was delicious.

I always love to check local bakeries out for there coffee & pastries. Hit this spot on a day they were selling a Nutella x Banana Croissant 🤯 they continue to provide delicious baked goods, gotta stop by here
This place is very hit or miss. Occasionally what I get is delicious, but then half the time the pastries and cakes tastes dry and stale.

The birthday cake that I ordered was beautiful and delicious!! The delivery was delayed by a couple of hours but I have no regrets for having ordered it from the Bushwick Bakery. The staff was very professional and courteous. I will definitely order from them again.
Such a nice bakery with a nice selection of goods at a great price. Completely worth trying out!
They have the best brekkie sammiches and pastries in this neck of Bushwick!
Great pastries. Hot chocolate and chai latte could be better - it seemed like both lacked milk to soften the flavor. Leaving this review as a recommendation for future improvement!
Sunny, happy corner with seating and fresh pastries. Breakfast sandwich 🥐🥓🍳
Great iced coffee and the breakfast sandwiches are always fantastic! People are friendly and its dog friendly!
Simply the best bakery & cafe in the nearby area, for both quality and price. The line that often forms out front is well worth the wait!
Iced vanilla oat milk latte is incredible! Love their espresso!
Food was delicious, best pastries in Bushwick
Coffee is on point, baked goods are made fresh daily on site, great breakfast spot
Great coffee, fresh baked pastries and a real staple in the area. A must!
Best bakery in New York.

I came all the way to Brooklyn for this bakery. It said it closes at 5am. Its currently 10:37pm on a Friday night. Its closed. Not cool! Please fix your schedule so future customers won't waste their time making a trip to your bakery.
Best croissant I've EVER had in my life. 🥐coffee is good.

Dropped by recently for the first time, really enjoyed their quiche and apple tart. Also my first pandemic coffee from the outside which was enjoyable. Only improvement would be to offer pre-ordering (in particular sandwiches) to save time waiting.

Stopped by on an afternoon walk and grabbed something light to eat. The food was great, loved the ambience and we chatted to the owner of the bakery and he was lovely. We will definitely be back to try more options
Please stop pouring hot coffee over ice and calling it iced coffee 🤦🏻‍♀️
It’s a nice little spot to grab and go. I had one of their chocolate croissants.  Staff was friendly enough.
4.50 croissant, egg, and cheese? Great selection, atmosphere, location, and the only bakery of its kind in Bushwick.

The tardiness of placing an order and receiving is the biggest critique. Staff has a laissez faire attitude to serving you something as simple as a BLT. 15 mins and I’m the only customer. It takes that time plus some before I mention it. And when I do then my order get attended too. I’m tall enough to look into the kitchen. Poor customer service just not worth your time. Food great but service is piss poor.
Authentic goods and quick coffee.... a delightful neighborhood gem
great bakery and great staff
(Translated by Google) Very good coffee special.  (Original) Muy bueno especial el cafe.
Great lime tart!
Friendly staff, cozy and great coffee. I love that this feels like my neighborhood spot. I get an americano every time and I tried the croissant yesterday. Fresh and tasty !
Very accommodating staff. They have some good coffee, pastries and brunch options.

Very charming place and nice stuff. Unfortunately coffee was really bad  👎 - cappuccino as well as ice coffee. I didn’t try pastry or baguette this time, but I’m not blown away with how it looks like.
Wonderful!!!!! Bakery Love!!!Everything😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍💓❤💓❤💓❤💓❤💓👍👍👍👍👍👍👍😊😊😊😊😊😊

THE LAZY BAKER. Baguettes are nevewr ready before 9.30am, maybe they forgot how usually bakerr get up early to make bread ready for breakfast. Croissant are tasteless, pain au chocolate passable. The almond croissant are always saggy and taste stale. thumbs down.
(Translated by Google) Super welcome, good little spot for breakfast!  (Original) Super accueil, bon petit spot pour le petit dej !

I am not sure why I have given this place so many chances, but today I have finally had enough. I stopped to get an iced latte and picked up a blueberry muffin to snack on. Luckily, this barista knew how to make a latte, unlike the times they poured me a cup of milk and gace me two shots of coffee instead of espresso.  I got home, unpacked ny muffin, and started to enjoy it. It wasn't the best muffin in the world, but I haven't had a muffin in a while so I was really letting myself go with this. I unwrapped the whole bottom of the muffin, ripping it into pieces for me to pick at, and in the corner of my eye I saw something move. I didn't think much about it at first, because I know how brains and vision work, but a few seconds later I decided to cautiously pick up a peice of the muffin. I was HORRIFIED. I swear to god, I have never had a food scare like this before. There was full grown, living, moving, wiggling MEAL WORM IN MY MUFFIN. It was literally scrunching itself out of a chunk of muffin still attached to the wrapper. I literally want to throw myself into one of those machines where they cut trees into little chips. This is not a life worth living anymore and I need to find a therapist to recover. I would also love to call them and tell them, but their phone goes straight to a full voicemail box. Lovely.  Please, spare yourself and just stay away. There are way too many coffee shops and bakeries around to do this to yourself.

Incredibly friendly staff and amazing food, pastries, and coffee. You really can't go wrong with this place, even if it's a little off the beaten path. Their croissant breakfast sandwiches are the best and the price is super cheap. Highly recommended.
Croissant on Monday morning was dense like bread. Slightly stale, definitely not fresh and lacking any crisp or smoothness. Maybe it was better when fresh? I will never find out. Quite cheap though.
Excellent bacon, egg and cheese croissant.
Found this place around the corner from my house, the coffee was very good and I could tell the pastries were fresh. Can't wait to bring friends here.
A big shout out to this coffee place Jewel tucked away in a "Warehouse". Exactly what millennial are looking for ( I am not one). Very rustic looking place with AMAZING coffee. Try it when ur around.
Great quality - very fair prices
My favorite bakery in the area--nearly everything they make is great, and at the right prices.
I'm a big fan, just a little touch of Paris in the middle of Brooklyn.

A very nice employee works there! When he’s not I’m not happy(I can be annoying) as the employees aren’t all as nice! I suppose working in customer service in other states has risen my expectations! But a morning joint HAS to greet you! That being said they have excellent pastries and such! Talent and service can be a great thing!

I love their coffee and desserts. Unfortunately the quiche is hit or miss, sometimes great, sometimes chunks of ingredients too large for a bite and undercooked. Nice service goes a long way as does location, so I return.
Fresh bread and pastries at a very good price for area. I loved the fresh French bread pizza.
Great coffee in a great neighborhood.
Best pastries, especially almond croissants, and coffee prices around.
Love love love. Why go to the deli when this egg and cheese is the same price and WAY better...

Cute little bakery in this area. I like the chill vibe and fireindly staff. Just a simple little bakery with treats, coffee and tea. One of the nice little cafes I've been to in NYC. Would come back for coffee and a pastry when I'm in the area.
Very cute shop with lots of breakfast options. Good coffee and pastry choices. Adorable decor and window seating.
Great local bakery making brilliant stuff.
Great coffee ,everything is baked on premises,
The service was friendly and the coffee is always good. They even have doggy treats for the furry ones.
(Translated by Google) Small and quant  (Original) Small and quant

Would not go back. Got a piece of quiche to go, and both I and my gf almost gagged when we tried it at home bc it was clearly gone bad -- smelled like dead fish. Second, they were quite rude about refusing to cut up a baguette for us when we bought. I've bought bread from multiple places in bklyn and I know it's a perfectly reasonable thing to ask, but the staff looked at me if I was speaking alien. Overall, not recommend.

I’ve been going to this bakery for almost 3 years now. When I first started going it was amazing, they had great baguettes, croqué monsieur, pâte sandwich and an amazing almond chocolate croissant. Over the last year all of those have disappeared from the menu with the exception of the baguette (which can be hardly considered a baguette- I would call it Italian bread because it’s so dense) Not only that but the quality of the pastries has also descended, not to mention that they’re constantly refusing to make menu items because they don’t have them prepared. I’ve kept going back to Bushwick Bakery in hopes of seeing an improvement. But after today I will not be going back.

(Translated by Google) This little bakery always makes me happy, the croissants and the chocolate rolls are good! To try: the croissant with cheese and eggs .... To die for! Adorable staff and small table inside (the decor is adorable) and outside if you want to eat directly on site!  (Original) Cette petite boulangerie fait toujours mon bonheur, les croissants et les pains au chocolat sont bons ! A tester: le croissant jambon fromage œufs.... A tomber! Staff adorable et petite table à l'intérieur (la déco est adorable) et à l'extérieur si vous souhaitez manger directement sur place !
I tried their chocolate croissant and was super displeased -- it was stale on some parts, which was super unfortunate. There also wasn't much chocolate on it. So again, super disappointed.
Great coffee good variety of pastries

Very good option of quiches, croissant bread pudding and French pastries. Fine coffee, great price.
Love this place, it reminds me of being home in Europe. Great coffee and pastries. Staff are warm and friendly.
Best bakery in Bushwick. I live closer to a vegan bakery but Bushwick Bakery is so much better and reasonably priced.The staff is friendly.
really good pastries and a surprisingly good spot to grab an iced coffee in the summer!
Great pastries, desserts, cinnamon rolls to die for, get it early! Glad you are in my "hood."
Amazing fresh creative baked goods and friendly staff! $1 coffee before 9!
Cute and warm
Great coffee, the best pastries in the hood and prices that make you happy.
